column288: Source: Statistics Canada.  With each monthly data release, Statistics Canada potentially revises any and all monthly volumes for the current year and previous two years (up to 36 months).  NTTO revises the volumes posted here once a year (after the February calendar Statistics Canada data release containing the previous December).  Thus, by the end of February 2022, both Statistics Canada and NTTO would consider 2019 monthly volumes posted here as final.  2020, 2021, and 2022 data shown here are subject to revision in February 2023.  Typically, revisions are a very small percentage of total.  Please note that the Canada volumes posted here are NOT seasonally adjusted.  if you seek directly from Statistics Canada revised data throughout the year, be sure to search for non-seasonally adjusted data.  Most easy-to-find monthly data from Statistics Canada website databases and analyses are seasonally-adjusted.

Source: Banco de Mexico (2000-2012); INEGI (2013-current).  Mexico visitor volume from January 2000 through December 2004 excludes land-border visitors traveling within the 25 mile / 40 kilometer "border zone".  Soon, these volumes will  be replaced by the the total overnight volumes (as provided by Banco de Mexico at the time.)
